<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 31 at 4:29PM EDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Gusty Snow Showers and Occasional Squalls this Afternoon...
Through about 6 PM, expect occasional bursts of heavier snow from
snow showers and squalls. Visibility will be under one mile at
times, along with occasional stronger wind gusts up to 40 mph.
While most accumulation will be confined to colder surfaces, the
heaviest snowfall rates will produce temporary pavement accumulations,
especially on bridges, overpasses, ramps, and less heavily
traveled roads. Motorists are advised to drive with caution and
leave extra time to reach their destinations.</description>
